The main purpose of this role is to provide administrative support to the
Eastern Fundraising team to help them research and approach new fundraising
prospects such as companies, rotaries and schools. Your role can be flexible
depending on your skills and experience with elements including data inputting
onto our donor database, researching prospects, inputting events onto third
party websites or contacting existing donors to wish them luck with their
Eastern office - Ground Floor, 8 Atlantic Square, Station Road, Witham, Essex,
For a chat about the role and an application form please contact the Eastern
Download theOffice Fundraising volunteer role description (Word, 116KB)
* Researching organisations on the web and keep accurate records.
* Making approaches to organisations or companies using email.
* Phoning existing supporters to wish them luck for their event.
### We are looking for people who are:
* Willing to learn about the work of Diabetes UK.
* Enthusiastic and able to keep accurate records.
* Ability to use computer and internet an advantage.
* Ability to communicate in a confident manner to a range of different groups.
* Someone able to commit to the agreed hours and provide reliable support.
* The opportunity to gain experience of working as part of a busy fundraising team.
* Full induction and on-going training, for example fundraising best practice.
* On-going support and supervision in your role.
* Experience of working in the charity sector.
* Reimbursement of out of office expenses incurred while carrying out activities for Diabetes UK, for example travel, lunch.
* Diabetes UK commitment to Health and Safety and Equal Opportunities Policy.
